<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFE6A41FF9191D11EEEBCC7" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFE6A41FF9191D11EEEBCC7" blockId="5.[109,1322,979,2237]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFFE6A41FF9191D11F5DBC9B" bold="true" box="[109,349,1928,1961]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Like other species in the genus, the Indochinese Thick-thumbed Bat probably roosts in dead bamboo stalks, rock crevices, and banana leaves, when available.
</paragraph>
